ce:section.ce:para:
To examine whether ratiometric fluorescent aptasensor can selectively detect the analogues of AD including GS, CD, guanine, adenine, thymine, cytosine, anion and cation (K+, Mg2+, Na+, Cu2+, Mn2+, Fe3+, Cl-, I-, Br-), amino acids (Cys, Arg, His, Ala) and urea were utilized to verify the selectivity and anti-interference ability (except for 100 nM of AD, all substances were used at a concentration of 1000 nM). As shown in Fig. 13
                        . No obvious interfering effects were observed in the presence of these interfering substances, revealing that the developed ratiometric fluorescent aptasensor had a superior selectivity for AD. Additionally, the linear ranges and detection limits of references demonstrated that the developed ratiometric fluorescent aptasensor was equal to or better than the previous reported AD detection sensors (Table 1
                        ).
